---
import "@/styles/globals.css";

import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import ContractText from "@/components/shared/ContractText.astro";
---

<Layout title="Omnitria | Privacy policy">
  <section class="max-w-full mx-auto px-6 py-12 bg-white dark:bg-black">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50 mb-6">
        Omnitria Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400 text-sm mb-8">
        Last Updated: 11/15/2024
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-8 text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
        Omnitria (“we,” “our,” or “the company”), headquartered in Guadalajara,
        Jalisco, Mexico, is committed to protecting the privacy of our
        customers, users, and visitors. This Privacy Policy describes how we
        collect, use, and protect personal information and any other data we
        process in the course of our software development services.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50"
          >
            1. Information We Collect
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            We may collect and process the following types of information:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>
              Contact Information: Includes name, email, address, and phone
              number.
            </li>
            <li>
              Platform Usage Data: We collect information about how users
              interact with our services, including usage and navigation data.
            </li>
            <li>
              Technical Information: Includes IP addresses, location data,
              browser type, operating system, and other device-related data.
            </li>
            <li>
              Client-Provided Information: Any confidential or specific
              information that our clients provide to us for the development of
              their projects.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50"
          >
            2. Use of Information
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            The information collected is used for the following purposes:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>
              Service Provision: We use the information to develop, implement,
              and support the contracted services.
            </li>
            <li>
              Service Improvement: We analyze the data to improve our platforms
              and personalize the user experience.
            </li>
            <li>
              Compliance with Legal Obligations: We process the data as required
              by applicable law or to comply with requests from legal
              authorities.
            </li>
            <li>
              Communication: We use contact information to respond to inquiries,
              send product updates, and communicate changes to our policies.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50"
          >
            3. Disclosure of Information
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            We do not share, sell, or disclose personal information of customers
            to third parties, except in the following circumstances:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>
              With Service Providers: We may share information with providers
              who help us provide our services, always under confidentiality
              obligations.
            </li>
            <li>
              Legal Requirements: We will disclose information if necessary to
              comply with a legal obligation, protect our rights, or respond to
              a government request.
            </li>
            <li>
              With the Client's Consent: If the client explicitly authorizes the
              disclosure of information to third parties.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <ContractText
          title="4. Data Security"
          content="Omnitria implements technical and organizational measures to protect personal and confidential data against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure or destruction. However, no system is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee the absolute security of data transmitted over the Internet."
        />

        <ContractText
          title="5. Data Retention"
          content="We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected or as required by law. Personal data will be securely deleted when no longer needed."
        />

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50"
          >
            6. User Rights (ARCO Rights)
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            In accordance with the Federal Law on the Protection of Personal
            Data Held by Private Parties, users and clients in Mexico have the
            following rights over their personal data:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mt-2">
            <li>
              Access: You can request to know what personal data of yours we
              have in our records.
            </li>
            <li>
              Rectification: You can request the correction of personal data if
              it is incorrect or outdated.
            </li>
            <li>
              Cancellation: You can request that we delete your personal data
              when you consider that it is not being used in accordance with the
              principles, duties and obligations provided for by law.
            </li>
            <li>
              Opposition: You can object to the processing of your personal data
              in relation to specific purposes.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <ContractText
          title="7. Changes to this Privacy Policy"
          content="Omnitria reserves the right to update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be notified to users through our platform or by email, and will take effect immediately after publication."
        />

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-50"
          >
            8. Contact
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            If you have questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or the
            handling of your personal data, please contact us at:
            <br />
            <strong>E-mail: </strong>
            <a
              href="mailto:legal@omnitria.com"
              class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-300 underline"
              >legal@omnitria.com</a
            >
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
